WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Breaking: the European Union has fined Meta 1.2 billion euros for GDPR
violations related to cross-border data transfers between the EU and the
United States.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:40.000
The fine was announced on May 22, 2023, by the Irish Data Protection
Commission. It is the largest GDPR penalty ever issued, exceeding the
previous record of 746 million euros against Amazon.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Meta says it will appeal. The ruling follows a 2020 decision by the Court
of Justice of the European Union that struck down the Privacy Shield
framework as inadequate protection for EU citizens' data.
